dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag c sub (A Martin) b Pollard 219 (149b 25x4 7x6 208m) SR: 146.97

dismissalComment.html: He is gone. He hasn't batted 50 overs till, but look at that score. Sehwag has mis-hit this attempt at hitting a six over long-off. Ends up skying this to Martin at long-off. Almost every West Indian has come up to shake his hand before he walks off. Rohit congratulates him too. And just before he crosses the fence, Sehwag looks back and raises his bat for the crowd. Lovely response from them

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina run out (Russell) 55 (44b 6x4 0x6 76m) SR: 125

dismissalComment.html: full toss on middle and leg, pushed down to long-off. He has played it with soft hands, takes Russell on, but the throw is directed at Raina's end and is deadly accurate. Raina is caught short despite the dive. Two wickets gone both run-outs. It was actually Sehwag's call to come back for the second after they had ambled for the first run

commentTextItems.html: and he's thrown it away. Skies an attempted slog-sweep and mid-on keeps his nerve to hold a really high catch

commentPostTextItems.html: I shall leave you with that, but do read George Binoy's bulletin and stay tuned for Sidharth Monga's piece on Sehwag's record innings. Goodnight and good luck.
It's been a day when India, after producing a Neil Armstrong in Tendulkar, have now got a Buzz Aldrin in Virender Sehwag. Unlike Aldrin, though, everyone will remember who Sehwag is.

Sehwag: "I was cheering for Sachin when he got his double-hundred and it's great to emulate that and break his record. I'd love to come back to Madhya Pradesh. The crowd has been great and thanks to them for cheering every run ...
"The pitch was great and allowed you to play your shots. I think you can only get a double-hundred when you're experienced. The last time I played 47 overs I got 175, this time I got 200.
"Rahul Sharma is a good prospect because he bowls at around 90kph and if it stops and turns then it becomes hard for the batsman."
Sehwag is of course Man of the Match.
He also gets a special prize of ten lakhs for reaching the world record. Is that the going rate for a world record?

Sammy: "Sehwag's destroyed bowlers all over the world. We bowled some good balls but he played better shots. The pitch was a belter and we got pegged back by their spinners. But we managed to get past 250. There was some hope because we had seen South Africa chase 400 plus. But they kept taking wickets and that made it hard."
Now for the presentation. Any guesses for the Man of the Match. Somehow the achievement of the double-hundred seems to hit home only when Ravi Shastri booms out what happened
"Well, whether you remember it or not, Sachin's double also yielded the same result- India winning by a margin of 153 runs." Well spotted Sash. India did win by 153 runs in Gawlior
All that will be forgotten though. This match will forever be remembered for Sehwag's 219

Well that was a rather tame end with Ramdin missing a possible maiden hundred. But the story of today is one man. Virender Sehwag. The spinners took nine of the ten wickets with Rahul Sharma taking three wickets on debut and Ravindra Jadeja turning in remarkable figures of 3 for 34 in 10 overs on a pitch where every other bowler took some tap.

Raina is caught short despite the dive. Two wickets gone both run-outs. It was actually Sehwag's call to come back for the second after they had ambled for the first run

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja c Rampaul b Russell 10 (10b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: and finally a catch has been taken. Jadeja plays an ungainly flick-pull to a slower short ball that has cramped it up. The ball is dying on the midwicket, but Rampaul runs in and takes it low

headshotImage.caption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Virender Sehwag player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Anthony Martin player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Anthony Martin player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virender Sehwag c sub (A Martin) b Pollard 219 (149b 25x4 7x6 208m) SR: 146.97

dismissalComment.html: He is gone. He hasn't batted 50 overs till, but look at that score. Sehwag has mis-hit this attempt at hitting a six over long-off. Ends up skying this to Martin at long-off. Almost every West Indian has come up to shake his hand before he walks off. Rohit congratulates him too. And just before he crosses the fence, Sehwag looks back and raises his bat for the crowd. Lovely response from them

image.caption: Kemar Roach player portrait
image.longCaption: Kemar Roach player portrait, West Indies media day

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma b Roach 27 (16b 3x4 0x6 21m) SR: 168.75

dismissalComment.html: that's more of what you need on such days. A yorker at 145ks. Bounces about 10 inches short of the stumps, and takes the off pole out. Sharma is beaten by the pace of it

headshotImage.caption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c †Patel b Jadeja 36 (35b 6x4 1x6 36m) SR: 102.85

dismissalComment.html: the attempted cut is edged to the keeper. That wasn't short enough, Simmons ricked back, went really hard at it but only managed a thick edge. The ball bobbled in Parthiv's gloves but he held on

headshotImage.caption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieran Powell player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kieran Powell run out (R Sharma/Ashwin) 7 (5b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 140

dismissalComment.html: and Rahul Sharma makes his first contribution. But Powell has run himself out here. Simmons just pushed the ball to the off side and Powell bolted down the pitch as if a firecracker had been set off near him. Was halfway down the pitch and Rahul Sharma just had to toss the ball back to Ashwin who removed the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels b R Sharma 33 (26b 4x4 2x6 38m) SR: 126.92

dismissalComment.html: and Rahul Sharma has his first international wicket. Its a topspinner and Samuels tried to cut. There was no sidespin and he's bottom edged it onto his stumps. Rahul's victory run has ended somewhere around the point boundary. He's clearly quite excited

headshotImage.caption: Danza Hyatt player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Danza Hyatt player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Danza Hyatt player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Danza Hyatt player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Danza Hyatt b R Sharma 11 (17b 2x4 0x6 19m) SR: 64.7

dismissalComment.html: bowled him. So this is why this bloke's in the team. A quick legspinner has done Hyatt through the legs. Hyatt was coming down the track, but he's got in a real tangle. The ball pitches outside leg stump, Hyatt stretches to reach the pitch but it turns straight through his legs. What a start to Rahul Sharma's career. Two wickets in two overs. Another five-for for a debutant?

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin c RG Sharma b Raina 96 (96b 12x4 0x6 133m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: and he's thrown it away. Skies an attempted slog-sweep and mid-on keeps his nerve to hold a really high catch

headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kieron Pollard b R Sharma 3 (4b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: short and Pollard's missed it! That was really short but it was the topspinner. Pollard had a big swing but he's completely missed the ball and it's hit the top of off. Rahul Sharma must think he's in a dream

headshotImage.caption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Parthiv Patel player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Andre Russell st †Patel b Raina 29 (24b 1x4 3x6 30m) SR: 120.83

dismissalComment.html: appeal for a stumping ans that's gone. Russell was attempting a sweep and he's dragged his back foot out of the crease. The ball from Raina was angled across the right-hander and it beat the bat. Parthiv was quick to remove the bails

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy c Mithun b Ashwin 2 (6b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: that's short and slapped straight down Mithun's throat at long-off. That's disappointing from Sammy. It was a long hop and Sammy could have hit anywhere. He's chosen to flat bat it in the air to long-off.

Kemar Roach has conceded the most runs in an innings (88) in ODIs for WI, going past Fidel Edwards's record of 86
Sehwag has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (142) in an innings in ODIs for IND, going past MS Dhoni's 120
Sehwag's 219 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for IND), surpassing Tendulkar's 200
